notes.title: youtube
notes.details:
ouTube is an online video platform owned by Google. In total, users watch more than one billion hours of YouTube videos each day,[7] and hundreds of hours of video content are uploaded to YouTube servers every minute.[8]

YouTube provides several ways to watch videos, including the website, the mobile apps, and permitting other websites to embed them. Available content includes music videos, video clips, short and documentary films, audio recordings, movie trailers, live streams, and video blogs. Most content is generated by individuals, but media corporations also publish videos. Besides watching and uploading, registered users can comment on videos, rate them, create playlists, and subscribe to other users.

notes.title: Henry
notes.details: Henry was a comic strip created in 1932 by Carl Thomas Anderson. The title character is a young bald boy who is mute. With the exception of a few early episodes, the comic strip character communicates only through pantomime, a situation which changed when Henry moved into comic books.
